<br>
Jewelry that I'd consider:<br>
<br>
Djarnn's Amethyst Ring<br>
2AC 9Agi? and 85hp.  The AC actually bumps up to about 4 or five because of the AGI bonus,  but 85 hp is SUH-WEET for a bard in a ring.  These are relatively cheap and easy to get or camp em.  Elord is fun.<br>
<br>
The Chardok Quest rings are good too, but unless you are willing to kill 3500 goblins in Droga.........<br>
<br>
Shadel Bandito Ring  is also a very nice one that is easy to get.<br>
<br>
Otherwise keep the 6/65's HP&gt;alles.<br>
<br>
Earrings:  the Orc Fang IS nice, it's got decent stats AND 15hp.  Super cheap.<br>
<br>
Earring of the Solstice:  Everybody and their brother excepting Kyepez has one.  This is a super duper earring.<br>
<br>
Sarnak Earring of Station:  I camped mine, but it SUCKS, however, if you solo the ent of chardok long enough......say level 56-60 you'll get one.<br>
<br>
Otherwise you're gear is pretty sweet and better than mine  I'd throw the dire wolf hide cloak away and get a Heiro, or Maelstrom or ANYTHING other than that.  The only thing worse is having a cloak of shadows =)<br>
<br>
Nice stuff =) <p>Baron Kyepez <BR>
